OL,5,Crules
OL,7,FThis in turn has led to water
OL,8,Fcompanies requesting permission to
OL,9,Fsharply increase bills to address the
OL,10,Fconcerns, but with public patience in
OL,11,Fthe firms at an all-time low their is
OL,12,Flittle appetite for it.
OL,14,FThe new Labour government has already
OL,15,Fannounced initial measures to tackle
OL,16,Fpollution but this is its first major
OL,17,Fmove to deliver on its manifesto
OL,18,Fpledges to reform the broken water
OL,19,Fsystem.
